1 Overview
**********

The ‘wikipedia.el’ package provides a comprehensive Emacs interface for
Wikipedia.
It builds on top of ‘mediawiki.el’, which handles the low-level protocol
details,
and adds higher-level workflows for editing, reviewing, and managing
Wikipedia
content.

   The package requires Emacs 29.1 or later and ‘mediawiki.el’ for the
underlying API communication.  Optionally, ‘pangram.el’ can be
installed for AI-generated text detection; when available, an "AI
Detection" group appears in the transient menu (*note Transient menu::).

Before using any commands, you must configure at least one
wiki site via ‘mediawiki-site-alist’ and establish a session with
‘wikipedia-login’ (*note Session management::).

   The package is organized around several core workflows:

   • *Page editing*: open pages for editing in ‘mediawiki-mode’ buffers,

     preview rendered HTML, and publish changes back to the wiki
     (*note Page editing::).

   • *Draft management*: save work-in-progress edits as local files that

     persist across sessions (*note Draft management::).

   • *Watchlist*: browse your watchlist with a grouped, expandable
     interface that shows recent changes organized by page, with unread
     tracking and background prefetching of diffs
     (*note Watchlist::).

   • *Revision history*: inspect the full revision history of any page,
     view diffs between arbitrary revisions, and navigate between
     historical snapshots (*note Revision history::).

   • *User inspection*: view user contributions, visit user pages, send
     thanks, and look up detailed editing statistics via XTools
     (*note User inspection::, *note XTools statistics::).

   • *Local mirror*: synchronize watched pages to a local SQLite
     database
     for offline browsing and faster access (*note Synchronization and
     local mirror::).

   • *Diff follow mode*: automatically display diffs as you navigate
     entries in the watchlist, history, or contributions buffers
     (*note Diff follow mode::).

   All commands are accessible through a unified transient menu
(*note Transient menu::).


