3.11 Transient menu
===================

The command ‘wikipedia-transient’ opens a transient menu providing quick

access to all ‘wikipedia.el’ commands.  The menu is organized into
groups:

   • *Page*: open, publish, preview, browse, and login.
   • *Draft*: save, open, and delete drafts.
   • *Watchlist*: open the watchlist, watch/unwatch pages, browse, and
     mark
     all read.
   • *History*: open page history.
   • *User*: user contributions, user page, user talk, browse user, and
     thank.
   • *XTools*: user stats, page stats, and top editors.
   • *Sync & Mirror*: sync page, sync watchlist, sync update, and mirror

     browser.
   • *AI Detection* (requires ‘pangram.el’): detect AI-generated text
     and
     clear overlays.  This group is only shown when ‘pangram.el’ is
     installed.

   Bind ‘wikipedia-transient’ to a convenient key for quick access to
any
command in the package.


